JOHANNESBURG – A protest is taking place at the Charlotte Maxeke hospital in Johannesburg. Demonstrators have reportedly locked down the hospital and strewn rubbish in its corridors. #CharlotteMaxeke academic hospital entrances have been barricaded by staff protesting - allegedly over unpaid bonuses pic.twitter.com/NFReFzCVet They're protesting over unpaid overtime. Police have been deployed to the scene. Last month, protestors, some belonging to trade union Nehawu, also trashed the hospital. This is a developing story. eNCA